Some tools can record Test activities ( "Thread Group" and "Request" )

1. Tools available for recording Jmeter UI test are,
     - "Badboy" software (Windows) : open browser and type "Badboy" --> download and install
     - "Blazemeter" - Chrome Plugin - (Windows and Mac)

2. Record a Test (Click on record start button --> set particular page url in address bar and click on different page link --> Click on record stop button)

3. Export as Jmeter script file (.jmx) Script 

4. In Jmeter Application -->click on "Test Plan" --> File -->Open  and select the script file (.jmx)

5. Add Listeners (View Result in Table, View Results Tree)

6. Run Test and View Result 


